    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-03-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 781.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith, for your information and the
                    embassy files, copy of a memorandum<note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">Printed
                        supra.</note> furnished to this Department by the German embassy stating the
                    intention of the German Government to send two officials to the United States to
                    confer with the presidents of the Equitable, the New York, and the Mutual Life
                    Insurance companies with a view to reaching an arrangement by which these
                    companies may be enabled to resume business in Prussia.</p>
                <p>I have communicated this information to the presidents of the three companies
                    named.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
